# WORDBANK dApp — environment template (PUBLIC; copy to .env.local for local dev).
# .env.local is gitignored. NEVER put an Alchemy/Infura/keyed RPC URL in ANY
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* var: those are inlined into the browser bundle and shipped to
# every visitor, so any embedded key becomes public the moment the site is live.

# --- Network selection (REQUIRED for non-mainnet) ---
# 1 = Ethereum mainnet / mainnet-fork (default if unset) · 11155111 = Sepolia
NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID=1

# --- Read RPC resolution (all OPTIONAL) ---
# Reads NEVER ride the wallet (owner rule). They resolve in this order:
#   1. /api/rpc server-side proxy  -> ONLY when NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_PROXY=1 is set
#      (forwards to the server-only RPC_PROXY_URL below). MOST RELIABLE path.
#   2. NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL          -> IF set; must be PUBLIC / keyless.
#   3. Keyless public fallback      -> built-in viem fallback() of KEYLESS endpoints
#      that can run the V4 swap quoter (mainnet: publicnode -> drpc -> ankr), each
#      with retry/backoff so a 429 burst is retried + rotated, not thrown. NOT viem's
#      cloudflare default (it fails the quoter eth_call -> a 0 quote).
#
# The dApp works fully with ALL of these UNSET (keyless fallback). The fallback is
# rate-limited under load on free RPCs, so for a reliable public deploy prefer the
# server-side proxy (option 1) with a keyed URL — see RPC_PROXY_URL below.

# --- OPTIONAL public read RPC (front-ranks the keyless fallback; pre-/no-proxy) ---
# If set it MUST be a PUBLIC / keyless endpoint (NEXT_PUBLIC_* is inlined into the
# browser bundle, so a keyed URL here would be exposed to every visitor).
#   Pin example (optional):    NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=https://ethereum-rpc.publicnode.com
#   Local Anvil fork example:  NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8545
#   Sepolia rehearsal example: NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=https://ethereum-sepolia-rpc.publicnode.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=

# --- OPTIONAL server-side RPC proxy (the RELIABLE option — key stays server-only) ---
# RPC_PROXY_URL is read ONLY on the server by app/app/api/rpc/route.ts and is
# NEVER shipped to the browser or committed (it is NOT a NEXT_PUBLIC_ var, and
# .env.local is gitignored). Put a KEYED, reliable endpoint here (e.g. Alchemy):
#   RPC_PROXY_URL=https://eth-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/<your-key>
# Then set the PUBLIC opt-in flag so the browser front-ranks the same-origin proxy
# (the flag carries no secret — it is just "1"; the key stays server-side):
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_PROXY=1
# In Vercel: add BOTH (RPC_PROXY_URL as a normal/secret env var, NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_PROXY=1).
# If NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_PROXY is unset, /api/rpc is never called. If it is set but
# RPC_PROXY_URL is unset on the server, the route returns 503 and the client
# gracefully falls through to the keyless public fallback. NEVER prefix the keyed
# URL with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
# RPC_PROXY_URL=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_PROXY=
